headline: Will Rinvoq’s Superiority Over Humira in SELECT-SWITCH Trial Change AbbVie's (ABBV) Narrative
summary: AbbVie recently announced positive topline results from its Phase 3b/4 SELECT-SWITCH trial, showing that Rinvoq (upadacitinib) was significantly more effective than Humira (adalimumab) in achieving low disease activity and remission for adults with moderate to severe rheumatoid arthritis who previously did not respond to a TNF inhibitor. This outcome highlights Rinvoq’s potential to become a more central immunology offering for AbbVie as Humira encounters increased biosimilar...
